issue_body:
There are a couple ways where the number of shards encoded in a scroll_id is 0 and upon a scroll search we hit [this](https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/928f89fa8e5be202e4fe84a8829a536d602b9c8f/server/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/action/search/SearchScrollAsyncAction.java#L89) SearchPhaseExecutionException.

Example 1: can-match skips all shards.
```
request:
GET /test/_search?scroll=10m

response:
{
  "_scroll_id": "FGluY2x1ZGVfY29udGV4dF91dWlkDnF1ZXJ5VGhlbkZldGNoAA==",
  "took": 2072,
  "timed_out": false,
  "_shards": {
    "total": 3,
    "successful": 3,
    "skipped": 3,
    "failed": 0
  },
  "hits": {
    "total": {
      "value": 0,
      "relation": "eq"
    },
    "max_score": 0,
    "hits": []
  }
}

request:
GET /_search/scroll
{
  "scroll_id": "FGluY2x1ZGVfY29udGV4dF91dWlkDnF1ZXJ5VGhlbkZldGNoAA=="
}

response:
{
  "error": {
    "root_cause": [],
    "type": "search_phase_execution_exception",
    "reason": "no nodes to search on",
    "phase": "query",
    "grouped": true,
    "failed_shards": []
  },
  "status": 503
}
```

Example 2: index pattern matches nothing.
```
request:
GET /blah*/_search?scroll=10m

response:
{
  "_scroll_id": "FGluY2x1ZGVfY29udGV4dF91dWlkDnF1ZXJ5VGhlbkZldGNoAA==",
  "took": 2526,
  "timed_out": false,
  "_shards": {
    "total": 0,
    "successful": 0,
    "skipped": 0,
    "failed": 0
  },
  "hits": {
    "total": {
      "value": 0,
      "relation": "eq"
    },
    "max_score": 0,
    "hits": []
  }
}

request:
GET /_search/scroll
{
  "scroll_id": "FGluY2x1ZGVfY29udGV4dF91dWlkDnF1ZXJ5VGhlbkZldGNoAA=="
}

response:
{
  "error": {
    "root_cause": [],
    "type": "search_phase_execution_exception",
    "reason": "no nodes to search on",
    "phase": "query",
    "grouped": true,
    "failed_shards": []
  },
  "status": 503
}
```

These responses should ideally be 200s with 0 hits.
